I'm very disappointed and frustrated with Bumble. Unbeknownst to me, and at random times, when I'd swiped right on someone of interest, their profile would not port over to my chat page, and even worse, they would never reappear. I reached out to Bumble five times about this issue. They did respond, but the problem was not fixed. Considering how much I paid for Bumble Premium, I'm not satisfied with the platform and will not be renewing my subscription.

Somehow, this app has become more and more broken with each additional update -- "unable to load" and "unable to determine location" are common error messages, despite a full WiFi signal. Messages fail to load unless the app is closed/opened several times. Ads appear while typing messages, which seems like a scam to increase revenue from a "cost-per-click" ad model. Very classy. This is on top of a removal of features that used to be available for free. Why would anyone pay for a broken app?

The app is constantly plagued by glitches and bugs that don't get resolved until multiple updates down the line, including inability to detect location, conversations disappearing then reappearing, crashes, etc. An app profiting off of loneliness has no incentive to improve because they know people will use it regardless.
